<section id="30-minute-fast-track">
<title>30-Minute Fast Track</title>
<p><b>Step 1: Understand What DITA Is (10 minutes)</b></p>
<p><b>Read:</b> <xref href="dita-intro-guide.dita">DITA Quick Introduction Guide</xref></p>
<p><b>Key takeaways:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>DITA = structured XML content that&#x27;s reusable and multi-format</li>
  <li>Topics are small, focused information units</li>
  <li>Maps assemble topics into deliverables</li>
  <li>Publishing happens through DITA-OT</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Skip to:</b> Section 2 (DITA mental model) and Section 4 (most important features)</p>
<p><b>Step 2: See a Working Example (10 minutes)</b></p>
<p><b>Explore:</b> the <codeph>examples/dita-html5-sidebar-starter-v2/</codeph> directory in the starter repo</p>
<p><b>Actions:</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>Look at sample topics in <codeph>dita/topics/</codeph></li>
  <li>Open the map in <codeph>dita/maps/getting-started.ditamap</codeph></li>
  <li>Review the plug-in structure in <codeph>plugins/</codeph></li>
</ol>
<p><b>What you&#x27;ll learn:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>What a DITA topic looks like</li>
  <li>How maps organize topics</li>
  <li>Basic project structure</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Step 3: Try Your First Build (10 minutes)</b></p>
<p><b>Prerequisites:</b> DITA-OT 4.x installed (<xref href="https://www.dita-ot.org" scope="external" format="html">dita-ot.org</xref>)</p>
<p><b>Build command:</b></p>
<codeblock outputclass="language-bash">cd examples/dita-html5-sidebar-starter-v2
./build/build.sh  # or build.ps1 on Windows</codeblock>
<p><b>View output:</b> Open <codeph>out/html/index.html</codeph> in browser</p>
<p><b>What you&#x27;ll learn:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>How to run a DITA build</li>
  <li>What HTML output looks like</li>
  <li>Where files are generated</li>
</ul>
</section>
