<section id="common-questions-answered">
<title>Common Questions Answered</title>
<p><b>&quot;What&#x27;s the difference between DITA and Word/HTML/other formats?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> <xref href="dita-intro-guide.dita#dita-intro-guide/why-dita-exists-the-problems-it-solves">Getting Started → Section 1</xref></p>
<p>DITA is structured, semantic, and designed for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Content reuse at scale</li>
  <li>Multiple output formats from one source</li>
  <li>Product/platform/audience variants</li>
  <li>Long-lived documentation with frequent updates</li>
</ul>
<p><b>&quot;How do I know if my team needs DITA?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> <xref href="dita-overview.dita">DITA Overview → When to use DITA</xref></p>
<p>Consider DITA if you have:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Multiple products/variants needing shared content</li>
  <li>Multiple output formats (HTML + PDF + help)</li>
  <li>Large documentation sets (100+ topics)</li>
  <li>Frequent releases and updates</li>
  <li>Multiple writers needing consistency</li>
</ul>
<p>Skip DITA if you have:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Single product, single format</li>
  <li>Small doc set (&lt;20 topics)</li>
  <li>Infrequent updates</li>
  <li>No reuse requirements</li>
</ul>
<p><b>&quot;How long does it take to learn DITA?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> Depends on role and depth</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Basic authoring:</b> 1-2 weeks</li>
  <li><b>Publishing/variants:</b> 2-4 weeks</li>
  <li><b>Development/customization:</b> 4-8 weeks</li>
</ul>
<p>Use learning paths above to accelerate.</p>
<p><b>&quot;What tools do I need?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> <xref href="../part06-publish/dita-publishing.dita">Publishing Guide → Tools</xref></p>
<p><b>Required:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>DITA-OT (free, open-source)</li>
  <li>XML editor (Oxygen, VS Code, or text editor)</li>
  <li>Java 17+ (for DITA-OT)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Optional:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>CCMS (enterprise content management)</li>
  <li>Docker (for builds)</li>
  <li>Git (for version control)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>&quot;Can I migrate existing docs to DITA?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> Yes, common approaches:</p>
<ol>
  <li><b>Manual conversion</b> (highest quality, most effort)</li>
  <li><b>Scripted conversion</b> (HTML/XML → DITA)</li>
  <li><b>Gradual migration</b> (new content in DITA)</li>
  <li><b>Hybrid approach</b> (convert high-value content first)</li>
</ol>
<p>See Developer Handbook for migration strategies.</p>
<p><b>&quot;How do I customize HTML output?&quot;</b></p>
<p><b>Answer:</b> <xref href="../part08-customize/xslt-customization-tutorial.dita">XSLT Customization Tutorial</xref></p>
<p>Two safe approaches:</p>
<ol>
  <li><b>CSS only</b> (styling, no structure changes)</li>
  <li><b>XSLT-import overrides</b> (structure + styling)</li>
</ol>
<p>Avoid modifying core DITA-OT files.</p>
</section>
